Japan Seeks Most Milling Wheat in Two Months in Tender

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-04-12T09:29:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/japan-seeks-most-milling-wheat-in-two-months-in-tender-1-.html
Japan  is seeking to buy 147,712
metric tons of milling wheat from the U.S. in a tender on April
14, the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said.  Shipment is set from June 1 to June 30, Masafumi Otsuka at
the ministry’s grain-trade division said today by phone. The
volume sought is the largest since Feb. 17, when the government
bought 153,858 tons.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It bought 5.16 million tons through
regular tenders in the year ended March 31.  Details of this week’s tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
